Read-only trace result: the normal boot/login/char-select/zone-in path does reach the non-native lock bridge, but the boot-relevant pair is the 24bpp terrain/source upload case, not DXT decompression.

**Non-Native Lock Call Sites**

| Call site | Requested format | Why it can differ from native | Boot-to-char-select? |
| --- | ---: | --- | --- |
| `src/engine/client/library/clientGraphics/src/shared/Texture.cpp:392` | DDS `sourceFormat` | `Texture::load()` creates graphics data from `ms_conversions[sourceFormat]` at `Texture.cpp:719-720`; D3D9 picks first supported runtime format at `Direct3d9_TextureData.cpp:295-301`. If `TF_RGB_888` is promoted, lock format differs from `m_destFormat`. | **Yes**, zone/load path |
| `src/engine/client/library/clientGraphics/src/shared/Texture.cpp:805-806` | `TF_ARGB_8888` | `Texture::computeRepresentativeColor()` readback of any non-ARGB native texture. Called via `Texture.cpp:742`, skeletal representative color path at `SoftwareBlendSkeletalShaderPrimitive.cpp:2111`, batch submit at `FullGeometrySkeletalAppearanceBatchRenderer.cpp:433`. | **No evidence in boot trace**; runtime skeletal batching path, not screenshot/editor |
| `src/engine/client/library/clientGraphics/src/win32/Graphics.cpp:1265-1266` | `TF_ARGB_8888` | Mouse cursor alpha hack locks cursor texture as ARGB. Differs only if cursor texture native is not ARGB. | Potentially login/UI runtime, but format mismatch not proven by source |
| `src/engine/client/library/clientTerrain/src/shared/appearance/GroundEnvironment.cpp:1782-1783` | `TF_ARGB_8888` | Reads gradient sky texture as ARGB. Could differ if the DDS native format is not ARGB. | Runtime terrain/environment; source-created cube writes at `1811`, `1838`, `1871`, `1920` are native ARGB |
| `src/engine/client/library/clientTerrain/src/shared/appearance/ClientProceduralTerrainAppearance_Radar.cpp:197-198` | `TF_ARGB_8888` | Representative/radar color readback from shader texture. | Runtime terrain/radar, not required for boot |
| `src/engine/client/application/TerrainEditor/src/win32/RadialTreeView.cpp:954-955` | `TF_RGB_888` | Editor samples shader texture as RGB. | **No**, TerrainEditor-only |
| `src/engine/client/application/TerrainEditor/src/win32/ShaderTreeView.cpp:968-969` | `TF_RGB_888` | Editor samples shader texture as RGB. | **No**, TerrainEditor-only |
| `src/game/client/library/swgClientUserInterface/src/shared/parser/SwgCuiCommandParserUI.cpp:1443-1444`, `1970-1971` | `TF_ARGB_8888` | UI command parser reads texture canvas as ARGB. | **No**, command/debug UI path |
| `src/game/client/library/swgClientUserInterface/src/shared/page/SwgCuiTcgControl.cpp:85-87` | `TF_XRGB_8888` | TCG texture is created with `runtimeFormats[] = { TF_XRGB_8888 }` at `SwgCuiTcgControl.cpp:399-402`, so this is normally native. | Not normal boot |

`clientTextureRenderer` does create compatible textures as ARGB-only: `TextureRendererTemplate.cpp:74-75`, `94`, so its normal render-target/destination locks are not a non-native path. `sharedImage` hits are `Image::lockReadOnly`, not `Texture::lock`.

**Concrete Format Pairs**

Normal boot/zone-in pair:

- `TF_RGB_888 -> TF_XRGB_8888` in D3D9 terms: scratch/requested `D3DFMT_R8G8B8` to native `D3DFMT_X8R8G8B8`.
- Fallback/parallel D3D11 bridge also allows `TF_RGB_888 -> TF_ARGB_8888`; see source comments and guard at `Direct3d11_TextureData.cpp:612-618`, `633-636`.

The relevant mappings are in `Direct3d9_TextureData.cpp:33-39`: `TF_ARGB_8888 = D3DFMT_A8R8G8B8`, `TF_XRGB_8888 = D3DFMT_X8R8G8B8`, `TF_RGB_888 = D3DFMT_R8G8B8`.

I did not find evidence that normal boot/login/char-select/Tatooine zone-in uses the non-native path for `DXT1/3/5 -> ARGB`. That conversion is possible through representative-color/readback paths, but the boot-relevant bridge is the `TF_RGB_888` promoted-to-32bpp case.

**copyFrom()**

Only engine caller found:

- `src/engine/client/library/clientGraphics/src/shared/ShaderPrimitiveSorter.cpp:569-571` calls `secondaryBuffer->copyFrom(0, *primaryBuffer, sectionRect..., sectionRect...)`.
- Wrapper: `Texture.cpp:825-827`.
- D3D9 backend: `Direct3d9_TextureData.cpp:640-681`.

The source and destination are same format: post-processing creates primary/secondary/tertiary buffers from `TextureFormat formats[] = { TF_ARGB_8888 }` at `PostProcessingEffectsManager.cpp:139-143`.

The rect dimensions are the same: `sectionRectWidth, sectionRectHeight` are passed for both src and dst at `ShaderPrimitiveSorter.cpp:569-571`. Coordinates are also the same. So `copyFrom()` is a same-format, same-size point/region copy, not scaled or format-converting.
